JOHANNESBURG - Passenger trains won't be disrupted in the Western Cape despite a multi-million rand debt owed to Eskom. The power utility had threatened to cut electricity supply which would have had a direct impact on commuters. READ: Soweto residents question Eskom debt Prasa spokesperson, Makhosini Mgitywa said the passenger rail agency has received a guarantee that Eskom will not cut electricity supply for now. The City of Cape Town claims it is owed R63-million by Prasa